<subSubSection box="[199,852,1538,1563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1538,2031]" box="[199,852,1538,1563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1538,1563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">Etymology.</emphasis>
Species named after the short size of its FWs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="408" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1538,2031]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1574,1599]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Within the genus, species characterized by the lack of outer tympanum, its FWs shorter than pronotum in males and females (
<figureCitation box="[532,606,1610,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1446,1468]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,187,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,179,1445]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., A, male holotype; B, female allotype; C, FWs, male holotype, dorsal. Scales 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224590/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[622,638,1611,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1181,1203]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,203,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,193,1160]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. A, male genitalia, pseudepiphallic arm, lateral; B, C, female FWs, dorsal (B), lateral (C); female copulatory papilla, dorsal (D), ventral (E), lateral (F). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224591/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">4</figureCitation>
B, C), its light yellow palpi, male genitalia (shape of pseudepiphallic arms, 
<figureCitation box="[219,284,1646,1671]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1181,1203]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,203,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,193,1160]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. A, male genitalia, pseudepiphallic arm, lateral; B, C, female FWs, dorsal (B), lateral (C); female copulatory papilla, dorsal (D), ventral (E), lateral (F). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224591/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">
Fig. 
<number box="[270,284,1647,1671]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A) and female genitalia (copulatory papilla as an elongate cylinder, 
<figureCitation box="[1045,1111,1646,1671]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1181,1203]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,203,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,193,1160]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. A, male genitalia, pseudepiphallic arm, lateral; B, C, female FWs, dorsal (B), lateral (C); female copulatory papilla, dorsal (D), ventral (E), lateral (F). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224591/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">
Fig. 
<number box="[1096,1111,1647,1671]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1538,2031]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1682,1707]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">Description.</emphasis>
In addition to the characters of the genus: Size medium. TI with only a small inner tympanum (no outer tympanum). 
<collectionCode box="[367,412,1720,1743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408">TIII</collectionCode>
inner serrulation: no spine before spur 1, 5– 
<number box="[942,955,1718,1743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" value="7.0">7</number>
spines in males (mean 
<number box="[1239,1255,1718,1743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" value="6.0">6</number>
), 
<number box="[1280,1322,1718,1743]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
spines in females (mean 
<number box="[321,357,1755,1779]" pageId="10" pageNumber="408" value="4.4">4.4</number>
