<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1181,1234]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1181,1203]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" box="[281,694,1181,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Luzara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[281,476,1181,1204]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">Luzara brevipennis</emphasis>
Desutter-Grandcolas
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[704,761,1182,1203]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[704,761,1182,1203]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, male genitalia, pseudepiphallic arm, lateral; B, C, female FWs, dorsal (B), lateral (C); female copulatory papilla, dorsal (D), ventral (E), lateral (F). Scales 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1279,1952]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1279,1304]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head dark brown (lighter in females), except for light yellow inner margin of the eyes (often prolonged as a short longitudinal line) and ocelli, yellow and light brown scapes and basal part of antennae; palpi light yellow, somewhat darker laterally. Pronotum dark brown, somewhat lighter dorsally; DD anterior margin and two small dots close to anterior margin (and a thin longitudinal line in females) yellowish. Legs light ochre, 
<collectionCode box="[1391,1436,1388,1411]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">TIII</collectionCode>
darker; femora with a lighter predistal ring, and a darker distal ring; TI and TII lighter with 
<number box="[1166,1180,1423,1447]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="4.0">4</number>
brown rings; 
<collectionCode box="[1335,1380,1424,1447]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">TIII</collectionCode>
with a small yellow dot above serrulation; subapical spurs brown basally, yellow distal with brown apex. FWs dark brown, the file and veins of the lateral field lighter in males, the lateral field lighter in females. Abdomen brown, the tergites lighter in distal half, darker basally with 
<number box="[769,783,1531,1555]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="3.0">3</number>
yellow dots on each side in laterodorsal position (often lighter in females). Cerci brown, somewhat lighter distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1279,1952]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1603,1628]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">Male.</emphasis>
FWs not reaching half tergite 
<number box="[621,635,1603,1627]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[652,731,1603,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1446,1468]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,187,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,179,1445]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., A, male holotype; B, female allotype; C, FWs, male holotype, dorsal. Scales 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224590/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
Figs. 
<number box="[718,731,1603,1627]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Venation very reduced on corneous right FW, only the stridulatory file clear; left FW soft dorsally, within the course of CuA. Right stridulatory file with 
<number box="[1267,1295,1639,1664]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="26.0">26</number>
teeth (n= 
<number box="[1411,1421,1639,1663]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="1.0">1</number>
); teeth small, high and largely separate from one another. Lateral field with 
<number box="[981,1023,1675,1699]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
longitudinal veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1279,1952]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1711,1736]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Similar to that of the other species of the genus, but pseudepiphallic arms bifid twice, first far from apex, second close to apex, the longest hook dorsal (
<figureCitation box="[800,867,1747,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1181,1203]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,203,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,193,1160]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. A, male genitalia, pseudepiphallic arm, lateral; B, C, female FWs, dorsal (B), lateral (C); female copulatory papilla, dorsal (D), ventral (E), lateral (F). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224591/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
Fig. 
<number box="[852,867,1747,1771]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1279,1952]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1783,1808]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">Female.</emphasis>
Coloration often more contrasted than in males. FWs very short, about as long as half pronotum; dorsal distal margin almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[570,649,1819,1844]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1446,1468]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,187,1445]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,179,1445]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp., A, male holotype; B, female allotype; C, FWs, male holotype, dorsal. Scales 2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224590/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
Figs. 
<number box="[635,649,1819,1843]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C, 
<number box="[683,699,1819,1843]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="4.0">4</number>
B). Venation lacking on dorsal field, reduced to 
<number box="[1250,1292,1819,1843]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
longitudinal parallel veins in lateral field, often irregularly bifurcated (
<figureCitation box="[801,870,1855,1880]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1181,1203]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,203,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,193,1160]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. A, male genitalia, pseudepiphallic arm, lateral; B, C, female FWs, dorsal (B), lateral (C); female copulatory papilla, dorsal (D), ventral (E), lateral (F). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224591/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
Fig. 
<number box="[854,870,1855,1879]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Subgenital plate small; distal margin concave. Ovipositor short, much shorter than 
<collectionCode box="[557,604,1892,1915]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">FIII</collectionCode>
; apex acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1279,1952]" box="[199,1299,1927,1952]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1927,1952]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Copulatory papilla long, cylindrical and sclerotized with soft apex (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1233,1927,1952]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1181,1203]" captionTargetBox="[155,1428,203,1152]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,193,1160]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Luzara brevipennis Desutter-Grandcolas, n. sp. A, male genitalia, pseudepiphallic arm, lateral; B, C, female FWs, dorsal (B), lateral (C); female copulatory papilla, dorsal (D), ventral (E), lateral (F). Scales 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224591/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="409">
Fig. 
<number box="[1218,1233,1927,1951]" pageId="11" pageNumber="409" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D–F).
</paragraph>
